TY  - JOUR
AU  - West, Kenneth D.
T1  - A Specification Test for Speculative Bubbles*
PY  - 1987
Y1  - 1987/08/01
DO  - 10.2307/1884217
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 102
IS  - 3
SP  - 553
EP  - 580
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - The set of parameters needed to calculate the expected present discounted value of a stream of dividends can be estimated in two ways. One may test for speculative bubbles, or fads, by testing whether the two estimates are the same. When the test is applied to some annual U. S. stock market data, the data usually reject the null hypothesis of no bubbles. The test is of general interest, since it may be applied to a wide class of linear rational expectations models.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1884217
ER  - 



